<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900411-0042</DOCNO><DOCID>900411-0042.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Bechtel Group Inc.:   Contract for Airport Project   Is Signed With Hong Kong</HL><DATE>04/11/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   FREST</CO><IN>AIRLINES (AIR)HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)</IN><LP>   Bechtel Group Inc. said it entered a contract with theHong Kong government to manage a $16 billion airportconstruction project, one of the largest such projects everundertaken.   The San Francisco closely held engineering andconstruction company said the project will take seven yearsto complete. It entails building a new airport, a suspensionbridge that would be the longest in the world, a rapidtransit system and a highway to China, among other things.</LP><TEXT>   Bechtel didn't disclose exactly how much it stands to earnfrom the project. It said the Hong Kong government hopes tofund half the project through private funds.   Bechtel's last project of similar size was theconstruction of the city of Jubail in Saudi Arabia, a $20billion project. The city is still under construction.   The Hong Kong project is the second major transactionBechtel has announced in a week. Last week, Bechtel signed anagreement with the Soviet Union to do a preliminary study onthe feasibility of converting a research center near Moscowinto a technology center similar to California's SiliconValley.</TEXT></DOC>